I don't know either.
@cbolisetti do we compute them?
@hugary1995 do we have patch reconstruction to compute nodal material properties for beam elements?

If you want to try you can probably make it work by changing every
#include<filesystem>

to
#include<experimental/filesystem>

but you're on your own for debugging any other incompatibility

This (how components of the Jacobian are being computed) is tied to the implementation of the beam elements, and how the the stress contributes to the Jacobian
@cbolisetti knows more than me on this.
For local_ke this is just some storage for the local Jacobian
This is the classic way of computing it, looping over test functions and trial functions, we do a quadrature based integration of the contribution of the kernel to the Jacobian
    for (_i = 0; _i < _test.size(); _i++)
      for (_j = 0; _j < _phi.size(); _j++)
        for (_qp = 0; _qp < _qrule->n_points(); _qp++)
          _local_ke(_i, _j) += _JxW[_qp] * _coord[_qp] * computeQpJac(jvar);

This reference could be helpful to you.
